OL,6,FKimberly-Clark said it is not possible
OL,7,Fto change its manufacturing processes
OL,8,Fin time for the UK Government's ban of
OL,9,Fbaby wipes containing plastic from mid-
OL,10,F2026.
OL,12,FThe UK Government announced new
OL,13,Flegislation to ban wet wipes
OL,14,Fcontaining plastic in April 2024.
OL,16,FA Kimberly-Clark spokesperson said:
OL,17,F"We have now concluded our
OL,18,Fconsultation on the proposed closure
OL,19,Fof our manufacturing operations at
OL,20,FFlint, North Wales. Regrettably, both
OL,21,Fplants at the site will close in 2025.
